Life goes by really  fast when you’re having fun raising four little ones 😅. Y’all today I turned 28✨🎉🎈!

A few things I’ve learned this past year: 
•Be patient.
•Trust God’s plan.
•Laughter is good medicine for the soul.
•Let go of expectations.
•Embrace the seasons of growth. 
•Friendships matter.
•My past does not define me.
•Healing can be messy.
•Forgiveness is a choice.
•Love is a choice.
•Jesus is near to me.
•My value comes from God and not my spouse.
•Children are a gift from God
•it’s okay to ask/receive help. 
•God is my strength and my sustainer. 

Thankful for the joyful moments and the trials that continually shape me into the woman God created me to be. Here’s to 28 !! 🎂💖💃🏻

Strive not to be a success, but rather to be of value. - Albert Einstein.

I went into marriage thinking I would successfully love Denisse with not only devotion, adoration and attention, but I would love her exceedingly well (even when we’re two totally different places)— an island girl with a military brat…. I didn’t know where to begin to love my wife successfully. 

Here’s what I’ll say — Throw away your definition of loving successfully. Spend some time learning what kind of love is valuable to those you love. Look up *Dr. Gary Chapman’s 5 love languages. Have the conversation. Ask the questions. Do the things your loved ones understand as love and you will leave successful love in the dust for a much better achievement: valuable love.

🎉HAPPY 2nd BIRTHDAY SAMUEL!🎉 🤩
Today we celebrate a kind, sweet, adventurous, fearless boy. My middle child. He’s by far the one I’m constantly chasing around, the one who gets out of his crib 20 times at bedtime and wakes his brothers up, the one who climbs tables and high places with no fear at all, the one who almost always gets his way and gets away with almost any everything haha. He gives me random kisses and hugs. Samuel is also so so loving, smart, tender, loves to wrestle his brothers, and hug his baby brother Zaccai. 

I am truly blessed to be his mother. God has been so gracious and merciful in my life. I look forward to nurturing his sweet soul for the next coming years. Enjoy your day Samuel we love you so much. I pray for a heart to know, seek, and love God with your whole life! In Jesus name !❤️

Did you know that when we compare our own lives and gifting to the people around us and it drives us to competition it is actually toxic comparison? There is a healthy way to compare your life to the people around you that are imitators of Christ just as Paul stated in his letter in 1 Corinthians 11:1.

God gave each of you a set of gifting not for yourself but for others and the advancement of His kingdom. Whatever you have been given from God use it for His glory with your eyes fixed on Christ. You will find freedom, peace, and confidence when you begin to walk in it. We’re not all to be alike, the body of Christ consists of many parts all working for the same goal. 

Next time you feel the temptation to compare and compete with a brother or sister compliment the work they are doing and celebrate with them what God is doing through them. You can learn more about this topic of comparison in my book Set Apart ❤️🤩

NICU DAY 5: Walking by Faith and not by Sight.

Everyday has been a blur. I’ve shed more tears in the past 5 days than probably in my 28 years of life. You can probably imagine what my eyes look at this point. Separation from the baby that spent 9 months in my womb so close to me now separated, I’ll take labor pains over that. It feels lonely but yet I know Jesus is near and close. Pain and overwhelming emotions come in waves. Despite every emotion I experience I know and I still believe that God is good. That He is a way maker, miracle worker, and promise keeper. Emmanuel has been such a fighter and his care team has been compassionate and knowledgeable. I am very thankful and grateful for my close and extended family and friends that have reached out, prayed, served us with physical needs and have done more than we can ask or imagine. This is God at work, this is God showing us that He will never leave us nor forsake us. He cares and He sees. Thank you for letting God work through your lives to serve and uplift during an uncertain time. 

Baby’s recovery depends on himself. We are all waiting on Emmanuel to work on breathing on his own. In the meantime we wait, pray, hope, and believe for full restoration and a healthy baby to come home to join his 4 wild brothers🩵 

Keep praying for our baby Emmanuel (God with us) 🩵🩵✝️

#nicumama

NICU DAY 7: God hears and answers prayers!

Thank you to every single soul that has cried out to God on behalf of Emmanuel and our family. Today, Emmanuel no longer has a breathing tube, his labs have looked great, his numbers are good, he is slowly going down on how much oxygen he is given, and he has tripled on his feedings. Praise God for his faithfulness. Today I was able to see his eyes for the very first time 🥹and today officially marks his original due date. 

I love you Emmanuel I can’t wait to hold you again close to my mama heart 🩵 

Continued prayers for his lungs to mature and for our family as a unit.🙏🏽🤲🏼
#nicumama

NICU DAY 8: Surprise !

Today I walked in to do my new normal routine of dropping off milk, pumping, and seeing my little guy. After sitting and praying over my little one the nurse asked if I wanted to hold him. I couldn’t believe it after hearing so many times “not yet” my mama heart was so so happy to be able to have him this close to me again and I changed his first diaper. One of many to come lol 🥹🩵
Thankful for each day and small victories along the way. One day at a time🙏🏽✝️

#nicumama

Upside-Down Kingdom ✝️

God's kingdom operates in a way that often contradicts the world's values. It values humility over pride, service over self-interest, and love for all. It turns societal norms upside down by exalting the humble, considering the least as the greatest, and emphasizing sacrificial love above all else. It challenges the status quo by valuing the marginalized, embracing forgiveness, and offering grace abundantly, which contrasts sharply with the values commonly upheld in the world.

One of the many practical ways in which we can live the inverted kingdom of God is to actively practice humility considering the needs of others before our own, to be open to learn from everyone, regardless of their state, and to be willing to serve without seeking recognition. 💜

Luke 9:48 (NIV) - “For it is the one who is least among you all who is the greatest.”

————
Reino al Revés 

El reino de Dios funciona de una manera que a menudo contradice los valores del mundo. Valora la humildad sobre el orgullo, el servicio sobre el interés propio y el amor por todos. Pon las normas sociales patas arriba al exaltar a los humildes, considerar a los menos como los más grandes, y haciendo hincapié en el amor sacrificial por encima de todo. Desafía el status quo valorando a los marginados, abrazando el perdón y ofreciendo gracia en abundancia, lo que contrasta fuertemente con los valores comúnmente defendidos en el mundo.

Una de las muchas formas prácticas en que podemos vivir el reino invertido de Dios es practicar activamente la humildad considerando las necesidades de los demás antes que las nuestras, estar abiertos a aprender de todos, independientemente de su estado, y estar dispuestos a servir sin buscar el reconocimiento. 💜

Lucas 9:48 (NVI) - "Porque el que menos entre todos vosotros es el más grande".

Jesus has given us a direct command not to worry about the things of this world. “For the pagans run after all these things, and your heavenly Father knows that you need them.
